article.headline: Fairfield 70, Canisius 51
article.story: BRIDGEPORT, Conn. (AP) -- Jonathan Han hit all five of his shots and finished with 16 points to lead Fairfield past struggling Canisius, 70-51, Friday night. Herbie Allen added 13 points and Anthony Johnson 12 for Fairfield (7-12, 5-4 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Frank Turner led Canisius (3-16, 1-8) with a game-high 17 points. The Golden Griffins, who have lost 14 of their last 15 regular-season conference games, hit only 17 of 63 shots (27 percent). The Stags never trailed, opening a 22-6 lead on Johnson?s basket with 7:39 left in the first half. Fairfield led 31-17 at halftime and the Golden Griffins, winless in 10 road games this season, fell behind by as many as 22 points in the second half.
